1)They are called wrapper class because they wrap the class around the basic type.
2)It is a mechanism of converting primitive data types into the object of wrapper class.
3)Auto boxing - The automatic conversion of primitive data type into object of wrapper classes.
4)Boxing - The conversion of primitive data type into object of wrapper classes.
5)AutoUnboxing - The automatic conversion of wrapper classes into primitive data types.
6)Un boxing - The conversion of wrapper class into primitive data types.
7)Wrapper classes are immutable in nature.

## Advantages ##
1)Collections only accepts objects
2)Performance is better
3)Serialization
4)Synchronization

## Primitive data types        vs           Wrapper classes
1)int                                       1)Integer
2)short                                     2)Short
3)byte                                      3)Byte
4)float                                     4)Float
5)double                                    5)Double
6)long                                      6)Long
7)char                                      7)Character
8)boolean                                   8)Boolean